Large bag holders are going to dump in every financial market. Good art will persevere. I get we're only up 1000% this year from the 2000% we were before, but I'm have a sneaking suspicion we're all still going to make it

Six punks (0.06% of supply) were just sold for under market value by the same account:

I get that we're all sitting here on a Friday, likely in a good financial spot, with no worries other than how our bags fluctuate daily, but c'mon, this is a blip in the large scale of things

"We're still early" = It's still ok to recklessly buy NFTs/shitcoins with no chance of long term monetary loss. 

Remember that anyone who says this likely has some very large bags to sell you

And to everyone out there sacrificing sleep, health, friends and family to flip every project mining for a rare or hoping the floor 2x's so they can sell and buy the next project: it feels so much better when you give yourself permission to stop https://t.co/y5DX6UmQzv

The crypto/NFT space only moves quickly if you let it.

Slow down, take breaks, learn and pick your spots. Opportunity will be much clearer and you'll have a higher success rate with fewer entry points.
